{% macro render_coverage_checklist(language) -%}
#### Coverage Quality Checklist

{% if language == 'python' -%}
```
Pytest Coverage Checklist:
- [ ] All public functions have unit tests
- [ ] All branches (if/else, loops) are tested
- [ ] Edge cases and boundary conditions covered
- [ ] Error paths and exceptions tested
- [ ] Fixtures are properly scoped (function, module, session)
- [ ] No use of .skip without documented reason
- [ ] Coverage report reviewed for gaps
- [ ] Mutation testing shows >80% score
- [ ] Integration tests cover service boundaries
- [ ] Parametrized tests cover multiple inputs
- [ ] Mock objects verify expected calls
- [ ] Test data is minimal and focused
```

Configuration to enforce coverage:
```ini
# pyproject.toml
[tool.pytest.ini_options]
minversion = "7.0"
testpaths = ["tests"]
python_files = ["test_*.py"]
addopts = "--cov --cov-branch --cov-report=html --cov-fail-under=80"
```

{% elif language == 'typescript' -%}
```
Vitest Coverage Checklist:
- [ ] All exported functions have unit tests
- [ ] All branches in conditional logic are tested
- [ ] Error conditions and edge cases covered
- [ ] Component rendering and interactions tested
- [ ] API mocking with msw or jest.mock
- [ ] Async operations properly tested (await)
- [ ] Coverage report reviewed for red zones
- [ ] No untested code in production files
- [ ] Type narrowing tested for union types
- [ ] Parametrized tests cover variants
- [ ] Setup/teardown properly configured
- [ ] Mutation testing shows >85% score
```

Configuration to enforce coverage:
```typescript
// vitest.config.ts
export default defineConfig({
  test: {
    coverage: {
      all: true,
      include: ['src/**/*.ts', 'src/**/*.tsx'],
      exclude: [
        'node_modules/',
        'dist/',
        'src/**/*.d.ts',
        'src/**/index.ts',
      ],
      thresholds: {
        lines: 90,
        functions: 95,
        branches: 80,
        statements: 90,
      },
    },
  },
})
```

{% else -%}
```
Coverage Quality Checklist:
